{{multiple issues| {{no footnotes|date=May 2017}} {{Notability|Biographies|date=June 2011}} }}
'''Bartolomé Clavero Salvador''' is a Spanish jurist and historian, specialized in [[legal history]].
He is a tenured full professor at [[University of Seville]] (http://www.us.es/acerca/directorio/ppdi/personal_3531). His works on [[usury]], [[majorat]] or the concept of State in the [[Ancien Régime]] (its absence, indeed), with a polemic content and a materialistic point of view, rendered him to be considered by historiography{{what|date=May 2017}} apart from legal. He was a personal friend and biographer of [[Francisco Tomás y Valiente]], who was murdered by [[ETA (separatist group)|ETA]].
