[[File:Topographical 3K gif.gif|thumb|500px|Timeline of territorial changes during the [[Three Kingdoms]] period.]]

{{see also|Timeline of the Han dynasty|Timeline of the Jin dynasty (265–420)}}

This is a '''timeline of the [[Three Kingdoms]]''' period (220–280) of [[History of China|Chinese history]]. In a strict academic sense, the Three Kingdoms period refers to the interval between the founding of the state of [[Cao Wei]] (220–266) in 220 and the conquest of the state of [[Eastern Wu]] (229–280) by the [[Jin dynasty (265–420)|Western Jin dynasty]] (265–316) in 280.  However, many Chinese historians and laymen extend the starting point of this period back to the [[Yellow Turban Rebellion]] that took place in 184 during the late [[Eastern Han Dynasty]] (25–220).

