{{Infobox Politician |name = Vasile Bahnaru |image = |caption = |office = Member of the [[Commission for the Study of the Communist Dictatorship in Moldova]] |term_start = January 14, 2010 |term_end = |predecessor = |successor = |birth_date = {{birth date and age|1949|10|24}} |birth_place = [[Micleuşeni]] |death_date = |death_place = |party = [[Popular Front of Moldova]] |otherparty = |spouse = |children = |alma_mater = [[Moldova State University]] |profession = |religion = [[Eastern Orthodox Church|Eastern Orthodoxy]] }}
'''Vasile Bahnaru''' (born October 24, 1949, [[Micleuşeni]]) is a historian from the [[Republic of Moldova]].<ref>[http://www.asm.md/index.php?go=noutati_detalii&n=2480&m=14&new_language=1 Vasile BAHNARU - 60 years]</ref>
== Biography ==
Vasile Bahnaru was a founder of the [[Popular Front of Moldova]]. He was a member of the [[Commission for the Study of the Communist Dictatorship in Moldova]],<ref>165/14.01.2010 Decret privind constituirea Comisiei pentru studierea si aprecierea regimului comunist totalitar din Republica Moldova, Monitorul Oficial 5-7/3, 19.01.2010</ref> and currently is the acting director of the Academy's Philology Institute.<ref>[http://www.allmoldova.com/en/moldova-news/1249045888.html First laureate of "Grigore Vieru" prize named]</ref>
== Awards == * "[[Grigore Vieru]]" Prize of the [[Academy of Sciences of Moldova]]; the Prize worth 30,000 [[Moldovan leu|lei]].<ref>[http://www.jurnal.md/en/news/moldova-science-academy-names-first-grigore-vieru-prize-laureate-98203/ Moldova Science Academy names first “Grigore Vieru” Prize Laureate]</ref><ref>[http://www.allmoldova.com/en/moldova-news/1249045888.html First laureate of "Grigore Vieru" prize named]</ref><ref>[http://mr00.jurnal.md/ro/news/vasile-bahnaru-este-detinatorul-premierului-grigore-vieru-180594/ Vasile Bahnaru este deţinătorul premierului „Grigore Vieru”]</ref><ref>[http://social.moldova.org/news/vasile-bahnaru-este-detinatorul-premierului-grigore-vieru-206107-rom.html Vasile Bahnaru este deţinătorul premierului „Grigore Vieru”]</ref>
== Works == * The monograph “Elements of Romanian Semasiology”.<ref>[http://www.allmoldova.com/en/moldova-news/1249045888.html First laureate of "Grigore Vieru" prize named]</ref>
